TENUATE (diethylpropion hydrochloride) immediate-release:
One immediate-release 25 mg tablet three times daily, one hour before meals,    and in midevening if desired to overcome night hunger.
TENUATE DOSPAN (diethylpropion hydrochloride) controlled-release: One controlled-release    75 mg tablet daily, swallowed whole, in midmorning.
This drug in known to be substantially excreted by the kidney, and the risk    of toxic reactions to this drug may be greater in patients with impaired renal    function. Because elderly patients are more likely to have decreased renal function,    care should be taken in dose selection, and it may be useful to monitor renal    function. (See PRECAUTIONS, Geriatric Use.)
